params.reserveAmount: the amount of DAI to lock

returns.learnMagic: the DEAL mintable for a certain amount of dai

params._burnAmount: the amount of DEAL to burn

returns.learnMagic: the dai receivable for a certain amount of burnt DEAL

params._wad: amount of Dai to send to the contract

burn(uint256).notice: used to burn DEAL and return DAI to the sender.

getMintableForReserveAmount(uint256).notice: calculates the amount of DEAL to mint given the amount of DAI requested.

getPredictedBurn(uint256).notice: calculates the amount of reserve received for a burn amount

initialise().notice: initialise the contract, mainly for maths purposes, requires the transfer of 1 DAI.

mint(uint256).notice: This method allows anyone to mint DEAL tokens dependent on the         amount of DAI they send.         The amount minted depends on the amount of collateral already locked in         the curve. The more DAI is locked, the less DEAL gets minted, ensuring         that the price of DEAL increases linearly.         Please see: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1hjWFGPC_B9D7b6iI00DTVVLrqRFv3G5zFNiCBS7y_V8/edit?usp=sharing

permitAndMint(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: handles DEAL mint with an approval for DAI
